<h2>About</h2>

<p>
  Snippetbox is a small web application written in Go by <a href='https://github.com/aartchik'>aartchik</a> that allows users to create, store, and manage text snippets.
</p>

<p>
The main goal of this project is to practice tools for creating secure server-rendered web applications using real-world backend patterns: routing, middleware, sessions, authentication, form validation, CSRF protection, database integration, and HTTPS.
</p>


<h3>Technologies Used</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Go (net/http)</strong> — HTTP server, handlers, and middleware</li>
  <li><strong>html/template</strong> — server-side HTML templates</li>
  <li><strong>MySQL</strong> — storage for users, snippets, and sessions</li>
  <li><strong>alexedwards/scs</strong> — session management (MySQL-backed session store)</li>
  <li><strong>justinas/nosurf</strong> — CSRF protection</li>
  <li><strong>julienschmidt/httprouter</strong> — HTTP request routing</li>
  <li><strong>justinas/alice</strong> — middleware chaining</li>
  <li><strong>redis</strong> — fast cache</li>
</ul>

